HEADWORD: Promptuary
<hw>Promp"tu*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining
to preparation.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Promptuary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Promptuary
<hw>Promp"tu*a*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>promptuarium</ets>,
fr. <ets>promptuarius</ets> belonging to distribution, distributing: cf,
F. <ets>promptuaire</ets>. See <er>Prompt</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<def>That from which supplies are drawn; a storehouse; a magazine; a
repository.</def> <rj><au>Woodward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prompture</ent>⟦br⟧
